cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.CT, cs.IT, cs.DM

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper deals with higher-dimensional categorical structures, which have connections to logic and proof theory. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper discusses the use of cube categories in homotopy type theory and univalent foundations, which have connections to programming languages and type theory. 
- cs.CT (Category Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with categories and their properties, specifically cube categories and their modifications. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the encoding of higher-dimensional structures, which can be seen as a form of information. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with graphs and their morphisms, which are objects of study in discrete mathematics.
